The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 Hunt for Kochi gun importer

 Kochi (PTI): Police on Wednesday launched a hunt for the man who imported from Dubai a consignment of furniture in which 86 air rifles and air pistols were hidden. 

 On Tuesday, officials had found 37 rifles and 49 guns concealed among plastic furniture, flowers, baby cots and blankets.

 A case has been registered under the arms act to trace the buyers, though no arrests have been made. Efforts are on to trace R.. Koya, the importer, who hails from Thrissur district, officials said. 

 In Kannur, Kerala chief minister V.S. Achuthanandan said communal fanatics were behind efforts to smuggle the weapons into the state. 

 Achuthanandan said this was part of the designs of communal fanatics to turn Kerala into their base.

 Girl killer commits suicide

 Mumbai (PTI): A 22-year-old compounder, who allegedly killed a 15-year-old schoolgirl for refusing his advances, committed suicide soon after the incident, police said.

 Chinnu alias Premchand Shivpujan Mourya, suspected for the murder of Sundari Tripathi, committed suicide by jumping before a local train at Kurla railway station on Tuesday, the police said.

 He had allegedly stabbed Sundari seven times after accosting her when she was on her way to tuitions.

 The police had initially said Chinnu was involved in the murder along with his brother Chandan, 18, but eyewitnesses confirmed only Chinnus involvement.

 7 buried alive

 Allahabad (PTI): At least seven persons were buried alive when an under-construction building collapsed on Wednesday.

 Labourers were asleep inside the building at the posh Civil Lines locality when the structure collapsed, police said. As many as 27 were injured in the incident.

 Tannery threat

 Kanpur (PTI): Tannery workers in Kanpur and Unnao districts of Uttar Pradesh have threatened a massive agitation against the state governments move to close down leather industries to prevent pollution in the Ganga during the Ardh Kumbh in Allahabad.

 Snake gifted

 Kochi (PTI): A Malayalam film and TV actor was presented a poisonous snake gift-wrapped in a box by students of a government polytechnic. Manu Raj discovered his gift after he noticed some movement in the package and opened it to find the 30-inch snake.

 INS Tarangini, the navys only sail training ship, set out on Wednesday for Lokayan 07, a ten-month voyage. The ship would call at 23 ports in 16 countries and cover 20,000 nautical miles.




